result.name: Vietnamese Cooking

reviews.text:
Very nice service from the staff. Homey and serve with great smiles. The lemongrass pork
chop is pretty good, so is the pho, coffee and milk tea. However, the deep fried frog is a bit under-marinated... Anyway, I'll definitely visit again for the pork chop!

I went to vietnam numerous times and also tried Vietnamese cuisine in several countries including Canada and the United States where they are more likely to preserve the originality of the Vietnamese cuisine. 

This place is tiny and simple but the food is delicious! Of course, in such a small shop (with such a reasonable price!!) one should NOT expect staff to cater you right away. But the staff were very friendly! 

After I tried the pho, I was pretty sure that the chef should be Vietnamese and that was true! Surprised to find somewhere in Hong Kong with good quality of Vietnamese food.

And by the way, the quantity was satisfying too! Hope that they maintain the quality because I will definitely come back!
Try try.  A little bit salty
Not tasty and price expensive for the quality
